com.ibm.ecm.api.coresdk.model.http

Interface IBMECMResponse


  • public interface IBMECMResponse
    Represents an HTTP response object after a IBMECMRequest call has been made. This response object can only be consumed once.

    This means if getBodyInputStream() is called and consumed, calls to getJsonResponse() will return read errors. The same applies if the two methods are called in reverse order.

    This class provides a number of convenience method to parse responses for IBM Content Navigator services.

      • getBodyInputStream

        InputStream getBodyInputStream()
        Returns the response as an input stream.

        This stream can only be read once. Calling getJsonResponse() ()} or getModel(Class) will also cause the stream to be read.

        Returns:
        the input stream of this response

      • getJsonResponse

        String getJsonResponse()
        Returns a JSON representation of this response. This will return read errors if the body input stream has already been consumed.

        This call can not handle extremely large streams. The entire response will be read into memory. For large streams, use getBodyInputStream() instead.

        Returns:
        the response in a JSON string format. This will return null if the response is not JSON compatible.

      • getModel

        <TYPE> TYPE getModel(Class<TYPE> typeClass)
        Returns a java class representation from the JSON response. This will return an error if the provided class can't be mapped to the JSON or if the response is not a valid JSON.
        Type Parameters:
        TYPE - the class type that will be instantiated
        Parameters:
        typeClass - the java class object that will be instantiated to represent the JSON response
        Returns:
        an instantiated object of that specific class type

      • getModel

        <TYPE> TYPE getModel(Class<TYPE> typeClass,
                     String propertyKey)
        Returns a java class representation from the JSON response based on the provided property value. This will return an error if the provided class can't be mapped to the JSON or if the response is not a valid JSON.
        Type Parameters:
        TYPE - the class type that will be instantiated
        Parameters:
        typeClass - the java class object that will be instantiated to represent the JSON response
        propertyKey - the property key to the property value that will be instantiated as an object
        Returns:
        an instantiated object of that specific class type
